 Introduction
Applicable Terms. In this document the term ‘TraceTracksAds ‘ applies equally to ‘TraceTracks’ and ‘TraceTracksAds’. Thanks for using TraceTracksAds. TraceTracksAds is a Mobile application provided by its authors, located at Hinckley, UK. Your use of TraceTracksAds is subject to TraceTracksAds Terms of Service and the Google Terms of Service ("Google ToS") and Google Play Terms of Service (https://play.google.com/about/privacy-and-security.html) (referred all together referred to as the "Terms"). TraceTracksAds  in the TraceTracksAds ToS. If there is any conflict between the Google Play Terms of Service and the Google ToS and TraceTracksAds Terms of Service , the TraceTracksAds Terms of Service shall prevail.
By ‘Location’ we mean any business or organisation that receives data from people in the community at large.
By ‘App User’ and ‘User’, we mean the person using the App and/or submitting the data.
By ‘Data Owner’ we mean the person who owns or provides the data.
By ‘App’ we mean either TraceTracks or TraceTracksAds.
Installing and using TraceTracksAds indicates that you are happy with and compliant to the following Terms Of Service in its entirety:
Access to and Use of Content. You may use TraceTracksAds as a support tool for capturing Trace and Test data. TraceTracksAds  is not a substitute for emergency services in any manner. TraceTracksAds  provides a data file. Processing of the TraceTracksAds  data file (containing your captured data) is not part of the TraceTracksAds  App. It is assumed the data file will be emailed by the App user or by the Location after gaining verbal permission from the Data Owner(s) to the Location and the Location will store the data for up to 3 months. After that time the data must be deleted by the location.
It is the responsibility of the Location to maintain and care for the data emailed to them from this App. There is no liability of the owners of the TraceTracksAds App to maintain the data in any way.
The data file email provides example data protection text “This data must only be used for purposes of sharing this data and for no other purpose - including not for use for medical, research nor commercial purposes.
Data retention (in physical or computer based format) is strictly limited to 3 months after the date of receipt of this data.” The User of the App must ensure that the Data Provider is happy with sharing the data and retention policy.
The App prompts the App User on the main screen and before sending the emails that the Data Owner is happy to share GeoLocation data, where the data is available from the device to the App.
The availability of Content and features will vary between countries and not all Content or features may be available in your country. Some Content may be available to share with family members. Content may be offered by Google or made available by third-parties not affiliated with Google. The authors of TraceTracksAds are not responsible for and does not endorse any Content made available through Google Play that originates from a source other than TraceTracksAds.
Age Restrictions. It is preferable users of the TraceTracksAds are older than the Adult age in your country. For example, the Adult age in the UK is 18.
Information about You. 
Use of TraceTracksAds  is at least according to Google's privacy policy, Google’s privacy policies explain how your personal data may be treated. TraceTracksAds provides a data file and it is possible to email the data file using TraceTracksAds. The authors of TraceTracksAds  accept no responsibility for whom you send the email. By downloading and accepting these TraceTracksAds  ToS you accept full responsibility for the use of any and all data created and distributed by TraceTracksAds  wither on the capturing device or from any other devices. 
